Sighted after we stopped at station.  School was very widespread - ending up surrounding boat in some directions out to 3 reticles.  Some subgroups were tight in configuation and others dispersed. They were swimming around fin whales, very closely, as well as hanging around the ship especially in the thruster wash.  They were leaping, flipping, slow milling and fast running.  It appeared that they were energetically positioning themselves around and over the fin whales as the fin whales surfaced.
